{
  "doc_id": "37863",
  "text": "MSAT vs CAT for shoulder pain indications most amenable to treatment with acupuncture. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] However, a systematic review reported that more research and higher quality research are needed to determine the relative effectiveness of acupuncture approaches in the management of shoulder pain. [CITATION_3] Our study has added to this evidence that the novel MSAT, which consists of acupoints far away from the shoulder with a necessary strong Deqi sensation and, most importantly, requires patients to move their shoulder when acupuncture needles are inserted for a certain period of time, is an effective approach for patients with shoulder pain.",
